\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. T. antoninae} Rouy & Coincy,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  37}: 165 (1890) ({\i T. portae} Freyn). 10-15 cm, with ascending to erect woody branches. Leaves 5-8 × 0·5 mm, linear, tomentose, sparsely ciliate at base; margin revolute. Inflorescence not differentiated, the verticillasters with 2 flowers only. Bracts similar to the leaves. Calyx 5-7 mm, the tube cylindrical; upper teeth narrowly lanceolate. Corolla 8-12 mm, purple; tube cylindrical. •{\i  S.E. Spain} ({\i prov. Albacete}). Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Sometimes considered to be a hybrid between {\b 9} and {\b 21} but the morphological evidence does not seem to support this view.
